All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Collision
    Stores all relevant data for a collision between a display object and the edges of the aquarium
    CollisionManager
    Provides functions to check if an object of a given position and size is outside the bounds of the given aquarium
    Core
    Core is intended to provide the core functionality for the top-level aquarium simulation class.
    DisplayObject
    The DisplayObject contains all the data for displaying something by a Core instance.
    Fish
    Contains all behaviours necessary to display a fish moving around a scene, each specific fish instance builds on and replaces behaviours inherited from this class to build their unique behaviours
    ICollisionManager
    Interface attatched to the CollisionManager class providing references needed for use by collidable objects
    IStateManager
    Interface attatched to the StateManager class providing references needed for use by updatable Fish tokens
    IUpdatable
    Interface attatched to updatable tokens to allow for being updated and managed
    JavaFish
    The JavaFish swims back and forth across the screen, randomly decelerating to a stop before starting again
    MathF
    The MathFish class contains a variety of mathematical functions commonly used throughout the program
    MathFTest
    The test class MathFTest.
    RandomRange
    Wrapper class for java.util.Random, adding functionality to easily randomise numbers between two values
    SeaHorse
    The SeaHorse swims diagonally around the screen, randomly decelerating and sinking before starting upwards again
    Simulation
    Simulation is the top-level class for the Aquarium simulation.
    StateManager
    Provides functions and data members to track the behavioural state of a fish
    Urchin
    The Urchin moves back and forth across the screen, randomly decelerating to a stop before starting again.
    Vector2<T>
    Stores a set of set of values, each defined by a different axis on a two-dimensional plane
